\begin{response}{Based on Fig 2, it is unclear why the decentralized method should be
used instead of the centralized one. What are the advantages of the
decentralized method compared to the centralized one?  This is very
important to answer to clarify the contribution of the paper.}
In many multi-agent systems, it is often desired that the individual robot in the system make informed actions that solve a global multi-agent task.
Moreover, due to computational constraints, it is often desired that individual agents make these informed actions themselves based on local information.
This then motivates Fig 2 as the centralized controller scales with the number of agents, we want to make sure that the decentralized controller approximately solves the centralized optimization problem without much loss in information from transmitting information.
\end{response}


